HEADWORD: Driftpiece
<hw>Drift"piece"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Shipbuilding)</fld> <def>An upright or curved piece of timber
connecting the plank sheer with the gunwale; also, a scroll terminating
a rail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

